        <h5>Waves Effect</h5>
      </header>
      <div class="box-body p-a-15">
        <p>
          <strong>Waves Effect</strong> can be applied to any element.
          It's enough that the class of element is <code>position-relative</code>.
          You can write any blank element that has <code>waves</code> class in it.
          It will inherit the element's own border-color and border-radius value,
          or it shall be black and rectangle.
          It is recommended to be <code>span</code>.
        </p>
        <h5>Examples</h5>
  {{#markdown}}
    <div class="position-relative">
      ...
      <span class="waves"></span>
    </div>
  {{/markdown}}

